			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I might suggest you look at EQ2 for several reasons:
<br />

<br />
(1) It is the exact opposite in design philsophy of EQ1.  Maximum raid size is 24 and most content will be directed toward a single group.  SOE's plan, so as to not cannibalize their own game is for EQ1 to be the Heavy Raiding game and EQ2 to be a more intimate experience.
<br />

<br />
(2) The vast majority of the ubers (and the moron that think they are uber) have already committed to WoW.   That doesn't mean there won't be the "win at all costs, damn the integrity" idiots in EQ2; but it should take a while for them to develop.
<br />

<br />
(3) Competition between guilds will exist in a more indirect faction with the end result being actual guild halls and associated rewards.  Guild size will not matter as the scoring system is supposed to compensate for guild sizes.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
